            <title>[LOG4J2-275] The send method in FlumeAvroManager quietly loses messages on a failed rpcClient connection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-275</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the FlumeAvroManager in the send method, the code looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Override&lt;br/&gt;
    public synchronized void send(final Event event)  {&lt;br/&gt;
        if (rpcClient == null) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            rpcClient = connect(agents, retries, connectTimeout, requestTimeout);
        }

&lt;p&gt;        if (rpcClient != null) {&lt;br/&gt;
            try &lt;/p&gt;
{
                rpcClient.append(event);
            }
&lt;p&gt; catch (final Exception ex) {.........&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if the rpcClient is null and the connect fails the rpcClient is still null and the method returns losing the event. I think this is a bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</description>
